# for pkg in bat broot bottom du-dust exa fd-find huniq hyperfine lolcate-rs lsd onefetch procs ripgrep sd starship viu xsv zoxide; do ./cargo search --limit=1 "${pkg}" | head -1; done

bat             # [A cat(1) clone with syntax highlighting and Git integration](https://github.com/sharkdp/bat)
bottom          # [A cross-platform graphical process/system monitor with a customizable interface and a multitude of features](https://github.com/ClementTsang/bottom)
broot           # [A new way to see and navigate directory trees : https://dystroy.org/broot](https://github.com/Canop/broot)
# du-dust       # [du + rust = dust. Like du but more intuitive](https://github.com/bootandy/dust)
eza             # [A modern, maintained replacement for ls](https://github.com/eza-community/eza)
fd-find         # [fd is a simple, fast and user-friendly alternative to find](https://github.com/sharkdp/fd)
git-delta       # [A syntax-highlighting pager for git, diff, and grep output](https://github.com/dandavison/delta)
# huniq         # [Filter out duplicates on the command line. Replacement for `sort | uniq` optimized for speed (10x faster) when sorting is not needed.](https://github.com/koraa/huniq)
hyperfine       # [A command-line benchmarking tool](https://github.com/sharkdp/hyperfine)
lolcate-rs      # [A comically fast way of indexing and querying your filesystem. Replaces locate / mlocate / updatedb](https://github.com/ngirard/lolcate-rs)
# lsd           # [The next gen ls command](https://github.com/Peltoche/lsd)
onefetch        # [Git repository summary on your terminal](https://github.com/o2sh/onefetch)
# procs         # [procs is a replacement for ps written in Rust](https://github.com/dalance/procs)
rff             # [rff: a rustic fuzzy finder](https://github.com/stewart/rff)
ripgrep         # [ripgrep is a line-oriented search tool that recursively searches your current directory for a regex pattern](https://github.com/BurntSushi/ripgrep)
sd              # [sd is an intuitive find & replace CLI](https://github.com/chmln/sd)
skim            # [Fuzzy Finder in rust!](https://github.com/lotabout/skim)
starship        # [The minimal, blazing-fast, and infinitely customizable prompt for any shell](https://github.com/starship/starship)
typst           # [A new markup-based typesetting system that is powerful and easy to learn](https://github.com/typst/typst)
viu             # [Simple terminal image viewer written in Rust](https://github.com/atanunq/viu)
xsv             # [A fast CSV command line toolkit written in Rust](https://github.com/BurntSushi/xsv)
zoxide          # [zoxide is a smarter cd command, inspired by z and autojump. It remembers which directories you use most frequently, so you can "jump" to them in just a few keystrokes. zoxide works on all major shells.](https://github.com/ajeetdsouza/zoxide)
